@startuml

title Game State Diagram

[*] --> WAITING : System Start

state WAITING {
    [*] --> PREPARING
    PREPARING --> PREPARING : Team Joins\nShip Placed\nLocation Added
    PREPARING --> READY : All teams have ships\nMin locations met
    READY --> PREPARING : Team Leaves\nShip Removed\nLocation Removed
}

state STARTED {
    [*] --> IN_PROGRESS
    IN_PROGRESS --> IN_PROGRESS : Bomb Thrown\nCode Redeemed\nAI Move
    IN_PROGRESS --> ENDED : One team remains\nor Manual End
}

state ENDED {
    [*] --> GAME_OVER
    GAME_OVER --> [*] : Reset Game
}

WAITING --> STARTED : Game Started\n(by Admin)

STARTED --> ENDED : Game Ended\n(by Admin or Auto)

ENDED --> WAITING : Reset Game

note right of WAITING
  - Teams can join/leave
  - Ships can be placed
  - Locations can be added
  - Game settings editable
end note

note right of STARTED
  - Teams locked
  - Bombs can be thrown
  - Codes can be redeemed
  - AI moves trigger
  - Locations locked
end note

note right of ENDED
  - Winner determined
  - No more actions
  - Reset available
end note

@enduml
